If there is a suspicion of anti-competitive behaviour in Germany, the contracting authority must report immediately to its professional level of supervision.
The Commission has to decide what measures to take and whether to inform the antitrust authority or the public prosecutor's office.
For example, in the case of construction services over 50,000 euros, the professional supervisory level must also agree if the contract is to be awarded independently, if the contract is not to be awarded to the offer with the lowest price or if the tender is to be cancelled.
